{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":686,"text":"This is the skyline\nof my hometown, New Orleans."},{"time":5766,"text":"It was a great place to grow up,"},{"time":8403,"text":"but it's one of the most vulnerable\nspots in the world."},{"time":12138,"text":"Half the city is already below sea level."},{"time":14845,"text":"In 2005, the world watched as New Orleans"},{"time":18297,"text":"and the Gulf Coast were\ndevastated by Hurricane Katrina."},{"time":21800,"text":"One thousand, eight hundred and thirty-six\npeople died. Nearly 300,000 homes were lost."},{"time":28010,"text":"These are my mother's, at the top --"},{"time":30281,"text":"although that's not her car,"},{"time":31735,"text":"it was carried there\nby floodwaters up to the roof --"},{"time":34283,"text":"and that's my sister's, below."},{"time":36381,"text":"Fortunately, they and other\nfamily members got out in time,"},{"time":40233,"text":"but they lost their homes,\nand as you can see,"},{"time":42448,"text":"just about everything in them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":45298,"text":"Other parts of the world\nhave been hit by storms"},{"time":47608,"text":"in even more devastating ways."},{"time":49592,"text":"In 2008, Cyclone Nargis and its aftermath"},{"time":52470,"text":"killed 138,000 in Myanmar."},{"time":55812,"text":"Climate change is affecting\nour homes, our communities,"},{"time":59244,"text":"our way of life. We should be preparing"},{"time":61692,"text":"at every scale and at every opportunity."},{"time":65349,"text":"This talk is about being\nprepared for, and resilient to"},{"time":69204,"text":"the changes that are coming\nand that will affect our homes"},{"time":71990,"text":"and our collective home, the Earth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":74544,"text":"The changes in these times\nwon't affect us all equally."},{"time":78896,"text":"There are important\ndistributional consequences,"},{"time":81206,"text":"and they're not what you\nalways might think."},{"time":83374,"text":"In New Orleans, the elderly\nand female-headed households"},{"time":86616,"text":"were among the most vulnerable."},{"time":88896,"text":"For those in vulnerable,\nlow-lying nations,"},{"time":90984,"text":"how do you put a dollar value\non losing your country"},{"time":93832,"text":"where you ancestors are buried?\nAnd where will your people go?"},{"time":98352,"text":"And how will they cope in a foreign land?"},{"time":100483,"text":"Will there be tensions over immigration,"},{"time":102560,"text":"or conflicts over competition\nfor limited resources?"},{"time":106056,"text":"It's already fueled conflicts\nin Chad and Darfur."},{"time":111048,"text":"Like it or not, ready\nor not, this is our future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":115865,"text":"Sure, some are looking\nfor opportunities in this new world."},{"time":119392,"text":"That's the Russians planting\na flag on the ocean bottom"},{"time":122416,"text":"to stake a claim for minerals\nunder the receding Arctic sea ice."},{"time":125848,"text":"But while there might be\nsome short-term individual winners,"},{"time":129110,"text":"our collective losses\nwill far outweigh them."},{"time":132648,"text":"Look no further than the insurance\nindustry as they struggle"},{"time":134911,"text":"to cope with mounting catastrophic losses"},{"time":136967,"text":"from extreme weather events."},{"time":139393,"text":"The military gets it.\nThey call climate change"},{"time":142248,"text":"a threat multiplier that could\nharm stability and security,"},{"time":145489,"text":"while governments\naround the world are evaluating"},{"time":148378,"text":"how to respond."}]},{"cues":[{"time":150425,"text":"So what can we do? How can\nwe prepare and adapt?"},{"time":154600,"text":"I'd like to share three sets\nof examples, starting with"},{"time":157631,"text":"adapting to violent storms and floods."},{"time":160600,"text":"In New Orleans, the I-10 Twin Spans,"},{"time":163288,"text":"with sections knocked\nout in Katrina, have been rebuilt"},{"time":166161,"text":"21 feet higher to allow\nfor greater storm surge."},{"time":170136,"text":"And these raised\nand energy-efficient homes"},{"time":172682,"text":"were developed by Brad\nPitt and Make It Right"},{"time":175544,"text":"for the hard-hit Ninth Ward."},{"time":178360,"text":"The devastated church\nmy mom attends has been"},{"time":181456,"text":"not only rebuilt higher,\nit's poised to become"},{"time":184128,"text":"the first Energy Star\nchurch in the country."},{"time":186760,"text":"They're selling electricity\nback to the grid"},{"time":188880,"text":"thanks to solar panels,\nreflective paint and more."},{"time":192527,"text":"Their March electricity\nbill was only 48 dollars."},{"time":195104,"text":"Now these are examples of New\nOrleans rebuilding in this way,"},{"time":199417,"text":"but better if others act proactively\nwith these changes in mind."},{"time":204313,"text":"For example, in Galveston,\nhere's a resilient home"},{"time":208096,"text":"that survived Hurricane Ike,"},{"time":210544,"text":"when others on neighboring\nlots clearly did not."},{"time":213160,"text":"And around the world,\nsatellites and warning systems"},{"time":216337,"text":"are saving lives in flood-prone\nareas such as Bangladesh."}]},{"cues":[{"time":220745,"text":"But as important as technology\nand infrastructure are,"},{"time":223857,"text":"perhaps the human element\nis even more critical."},{"time":227593,"text":"We need better planning\nand systems for evacuation."},{"time":230976,"text":"We need to better understand\nhow people make decisions"},{"time":234065,"text":"in times of crisis, and why."},{"time":236161,"text":"While it's true that many who died in Katrina\ndid not have access to transportation,"},{"time":240273,"text":"others who did refused to leave\nas the storm approached,"},{"time":243473,"text":"often because available\ntransportation and shelters"},{"time":247295,"text":"refused to allow them to take their pets."},{"time":249809,"text":"Imagine leaving behind your own pet\nin an evacuation or a rescue."},{"time":254829,"text":"Fortunately in 2006, Congress passed"},{"time":257704,"text":"the Pet Evacuation and Transportation\nStandards Act (Laughter)"},{"time":261178,"text":"— it spells \"PETS\" — to change that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":265716,"text":"Second, preparing for heat and drought."},{"time":268601,"text":"Farmers are facing challenges\nof drought from Asia"},{"time":271474,"text":"to Africa, from Australia to Oklahoma,"},{"time":273978,"text":"while heat waves linked\nwith climate change"},{"time":276345,"text":"have killed tens of thousands of people"},{"time":278746,"text":"in Western Europe in 2003,\nand again in Russia in 2010."},{"time":284978,"text":"In Ethiopia, 70 percent, that's 7-0\npercent of the population,"},{"time":289929,"text":"depends on rainfall for its livelihood."},{"time":292538,"text":"Oxfam and Swiss Re, together\nwith Rockefeller Foundation,"},{"time":296250,"text":"are helping farmers like this\none build hillside terraces"},{"time":299906,"text":"and find other ways to conserve water,"},{"time":302537,"text":"but they're also providing for insurance\nwhen the droughts do come."},{"time":306538,"text":"The stability this provides\nis giving the farmers"},{"time":308896,"text":"the confidence to invest."},{"time":310722,"text":"It's giving them access\nto affordable credit."},{"time":313364,"text":"It's allowing them to become\nmore productive so that"},{"time":315012,"text":"they can afford their own insurance\nover time, without assistance."},{"time":318922,"text":"It's a virtuous cycle,\nand one that could be replicated"},{"time":321566,"text":"throughout the developing world."},{"time":323917,"text":"After a lethal 1995 heat wave"},{"time":326762,"text":"turned refrigerator\ntrucks from the popular"},{"time":329362,"text":"Taste of Chicago festival\ninto makeshift morgues,"},{"time":332555,"text":"Chicago became a recognized leader,"},{"time":334802,"text":"tamping down on the urban\nheat island impact"},{"time":337633,"text":"through opening cooling centers,"},{"time":339650,"text":"outreach to vulnerable\nneighborhoods, planting trees,"},{"time":342859,"text":"creating cool white\nor vegetated green roofs."},{"time":345786,"text":"This is City Hall's green roof, next to Cook\nCounty's [portion of the] roof,"},{"time":349430,"text":"which is 77 degrees Fahrenheit\nhotter at the surface."},{"time":352946,"text":"Washington, D.C., last year,\nactually led the nation"},{"time":357042,"text":"in new green roofs installed,\nand they're funding this in part"},{"time":360354,"text":"thanks to a five-cent tax on plastic bags."},{"time":363808,"text":"They're splitting the cost\nof installing these green roofs"},{"time":366594,"text":"with home and building owners."},{"time":368306,"text":"The roofs not only temper\nurban heat island impact"},{"time":370837,"text":"but they save energy, and therefore money,"},{"time":373194,"text":"the emissions that cause climate change,"},{"time":375347,"text":"and they also reduce stormwater runoff."},{"time":377842,"text":"So some solutions to heat can\nprovide for win-win-wins."}]},{"cues":[{"time":382594,"text":"Third, adapting to rising seas."},{"time":386356,"text":"Sea level rise threatens coastal\necosystems, agriculture,"},{"time":390002,"text":"even major cities. This\nis what one to two meters"},{"time":393386,"text":"of sea level rise looks\nlike in the Mekong Delta."},{"time":396386,"text":"That's where half\nof Vietnam's rice is grown."},{"time":399037,"text":"Infrastructure is going to be affected."},{"time":402170,"text":"Airports around the world\nare located on the coast."},{"time":404690,"text":"It makes sense, right? There's open space,"},{"time":406714,"text":"the planes can take off and land\nwithout worrying about"},{"time":409359,"text":"creating noise or avoiding tall buildings."},{"time":411574,"text":"Here's just one example,\nSan Francisco Airport,"},{"time":414710,"text":"with 16 inches or more of flooding."},{"time":417424,"text":"Imagine the staggering cost of protecting"},{"time":420326,"text":"this vital infrastructure with levees."},{"time":423680,"text":"But there might be some changes in store"},{"time":425609,"text":"that you might not imagine. For example,"},{"time":427816,"text":"planes require more runway for takeoff"},{"time":430377,"text":"because the heated, less dense\nair, provides for less lift."},{"time":434243,"text":"San Francisco is also\nspending 40 million dollars"},{"time":437728,"text":"to rethink and redesign its\nwater and sewage treatment,"},{"time":440918,"text":"as water outfall pipes like this\none can be flooded with seawater,"},{"time":444248,"text":"causing backups at the plant,\nharming the bacteria"},{"time":447217,"text":"that are needed to treat the waste."},{"time":448908,"text":"So these outfall pipes\nhave been retrofitted"},{"time":451028,"text":"to shut seawater\noff from entering the system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":454184,"text":"Beyond these technical solutions, our work"},{"time":457112,"text":"at the Georgetown Climate\nCenter with communities"},{"time":458880,"text":"encourages them to look at what existing\nlegal and policy tools are available"},{"time":462648,"text":"and to consider how they can\naccommodate change."},{"time":466224,"text":"For example, in land use,\nwhich areas do you want"},{"time":469176,"text":"to protect, through adding\na seawall, for example,"},{"time":472136,"text":"alter, by raising\nbuildings, or retreat from,"},{"time":475912,"text":"to allow the migration\nof important natural systems,"},{"time":478720,"text":"such as wetlands or beaches?"},{"time":481447,"text":"Other examples to consider. In the U.K.,"},{"time":483704,"text":"the Thames Barrier protects\nLondon from storm surge."},{"time":487158,"text":"The Asian Cities Climate\n[Change] Resilience Network"},{"time":489704,"text":"is restoring vital ecosystems\nlike forest mangroves."},{"time":492902,"text":"These are not only important\necosystems in their own right,"},{"time":495992,"text":"but they also serve as a buffer\nto protect inland communities."},{"time":500288,"text":"New York City is incredibly\nvulnerable to storms,"},{"time":504000,"text":"as you can see from this clever\nsign, and to sea level rise,"},{"time":507683,"text":"and to storm surge, as you can\nsee from the subway flooding."},{"time":510843,"text":"But back above ground, these\nraised ventilation grates"},{"time":514253,"text":"for the subway system show\nthat solutions can be both"},{"time":516801,"text":"functional and attractive.\nIn fact, in New York,"},{"time":519467,"text":"San Francisco and London,\ndesigners have envisioned"},{"time":522619,"text":"ways to better integrate\nthe natural and built environments"},{"time":525507,"text":"with climate change in mind."},{"time":527915,"text":"I think these are inspiring\nexamples of what's possible"},{"time":530819,"text":"when we feel empowered to plan\nfor a world that will be different."}]},{"cues":[{"time":533986,"text":"But now, a word of caution."},{"time":537004,"text":"Adaptation's too important\nto be left to the experts."},{"time":539883,"text":"Why? Well, there are no experts."},{"time":543235,"text":"We're entering uncharted\nterritory, and yet"},{"time":546555,"text":"our expertise and our systems\nare based on the past."},{"time":550451,"text":"\"Stationarity\" is the notion\nthat we can anticipate the future"},{"time":553428,"text":"based on the past, and plan accordingly,"},{"time":556299,"text":"and this principle governs\nmuch of our engineering,"},{"time":558752,"text":"our design of critical\ninfrastructure, city water systems,"},{"time":561801,"text":"building codes, even water rights\nand other legal precedents."},{"time":565922,"text":"But we can simply no longer\nrely on established norms."},{"time":569051,"text":"We're operating outside the bounds\nof CO2 concentrations"},{"time":573411,"text":"that the planet has seen\nfor hundreds of thousands of years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":577918,"text":"The larger point I'm\ntrying to make is this."},{"time":581231,"text":"It's up to us to look\nat our homes and our communities,"},{"time":584927,"text":"our vulnerabilities\nand our exposures to risk,"},{"time":587614,"text":"and to find ways to not just\nsurvive, but to thrive,"},{"time":591159,"text":"and it's up to us to plan and to prepare"},{"time":593903,"text":"and to call on our government\nleaders and require them"},{"time":596499,"text":"to do the same, even while they address"},{"time":598559,"text":"the underlying causes of climate change."},{"time":601798,"text":"There are no quick fixes."},{"time":603454,"text":"There are no one-size-fits-all solutions."},{"time":606729,"text":"We're all learning by doing."},{"time":608638,"text":"But the operative word is doing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":612743,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":614046,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}